  "market_context": "Bullish daily trend with higher highs and higher lows; price retraced into a daily internal range liquidity (fair value gap), then confirmed continuation via hourly change in state of delivery after sweeping a low.",
  "key_observation": "Price respected the daily fair value gap (IRL) as support during retracement, then continued upward toward the daily external range liquidity (swing high) after hourly CISD confirmation.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified bullish daily trend structure with higher highs and higher lows on the daily chart.",
    "Step 2: Noted price retracing into a daily fair value gap, which served as internal range liquidity (IRL) and was respected as support.",
    "Step 3: Dropped to hourly timeframe to confirm change in state of delivery (CISD) after price swept a prior low.",
    "Step 4: Recognized a new bullish order block formed after closing above the down-close candles that created the swept low.",
    "Step 5: Entered long with stop below the swept low, targeting 2R first, then runners toward the daily external range liquidity (high).",
    "Step 6: Observed price hitting 2R, retracing again into the IRL (FVG), then continuing to reach the daily ERL (high)."
  ],
  "outcome": "2R target hit, then price reached daily external range liquidity (high); trade successful with runners taken to ERL.",
  "lessons": "Daily IRL (FVG) provides high-probability support in trending markets; hourly CISD confirms entry timing; ERL serves as natural structural target after continuation. Mechanical alignment of HTF bias, IRL, and LTF CISD yields high-probability setups.",
